nce in teaching elementary school  middle school science  and Physics  Earth Science  and Physical Science at the high school level  She has an undergraduate degree from UNC CH  a master s degree from UNC G  and is national board certified   Jacob Taylor  STEM Instructor  STEM Academy  Pittsylvania County Schools  Jacob Taylor has been teaching for 6 years and is an alumni of Bridgewater College with a degree in Physics  He has taught physics  calculus  and various math levels   Jill Collins  STEM Instructor   STEM Academy  Pittsylvania County Schools Mrs  Collins has taught for 20 years with experience in middle school science  Life Science  and STEM summer camps  She is a graduate of Averett University with a Bachelor s Degree in Physical Education and a Master s Degree in Education with a Biology Concentration    NASA Ignite  in the Classroom   Grades 3 8 Using the NASA Ignite  website  attendees will receive a hands on approach to teaching about our Universe  Attendees will be given the website and a short tutorial on how to access it  Attendees will then be able to participate in a lesson from the site  Attendees will see how everyday resources can be integrated into their curriculum  and that it doesn t take a lot of prep work on the classroom teacher s part  This meets several Language  Mathematics  Social Studies and Sciences SOL s  This workshop covers integrated STEM for teachers and administrators with students in grades 3 8  Instructor   Kristie Meyers  Teacher  St  Leo The Great Catholic School Science nerd and student professed tree hugger  14 years of combined public and private school teaching experience  BS in Elementary education and MS in curriculum instruction and design  NASA Ignite  Certified Educator  Always looking to integrate a love of science and STEM into classrooms in order to spark student interests and prepare them with real life skills and a love of science  Niche Bots   Grades 3 4 In this hand s on workshop  participants will construct a Niche bot that contains a working circuit  The bot must represent its niche  have adaptations for its habitat  and characteristics of its animal type  The bot must include a working pager motor and move independently  Participants will create a unique name for each Niche bot and design a trading card using appropriate iPad apps  As a group  we will use the trading cards to discuss each Niche bot s role in the food web  Target Virginia SOL Standards  Science 3 4  3 5  3 6  4 5  4 3  English 3 9  3 10  3 12  4 7  4 8  Math 3 9  4 6  4 7  C T 3 5 2  C T 3 5 10  C T 3 5 11 Supporting Virginia SOL Standards  C T 3 5    This workshop covers science for teachers with students in grades 3 4  Instructors     Meg Swecker Instructional Technology Resource Teacher  Roanoke County Public Schools Meg Swecker is the Coordinator of Technology Integration and an ITRT for Roanoke County Public Schools  She collaborates with K 8 teachers in the use of instructional technology  STEM  Children s Engineering  and Project Based Learning   James Decker  4th Grade Teacher  Green Valley Elementary School Not all about the trifold board  Building grit and curiosity through engineering design   Grades 5 8  Administrators It takes more than the traditional science fair to ensure that your students develop the digital age skills and habits of mind to make them great innovators and problem solvers  Learn how to overcome three critical barriers to student centered learning using free resources from the Army Educational Outreach Program  This workshop is hands on make it take it  and teachers leave with ideas they can use Monday morning  This workshop covers integrated stem for teachers and administrators with students in grades 5 8  Instructor   Jill Latchana  Assistant Program Manager  National Science Teachers Association Jill Latchana is a former middle school science teacher livin  the dream at the National Science Teachers Association  Utilizing her 15 years of experience in professional