anish language as well as upper level courses in 20th century Spanish  Peninsular  cultural studies  film  and Spanish for Business  She is the co author of Sendas literarias  2nd  3rd editions  Pearson School  Vistas  Introducci n a la lengua espa ola  1st ed  VHL HE  and Ventanas   Curso intermedio de lengua espa ola 1st ed  VHL HE  and over 15 essay publications  In their course evaluations  cadets consistently cite the incorporation of instructional technology as  particularly effective about this instructor s teaching  and project based assessment  ePortfolios  digital storytelling  problem solving  as the  course activity       that provided the most intellectual stimulation  A practitioner of ePortfolio assessment since 2005  Professor Dellinger served as the Institute s first director of the VMI ePortfolio Initiative  Cadets W  Schafer Wymond  16 and Max Groene  16 Power your Classroom with Renewable Energy   Grades 3 8  Administrators During this workshop participants will learn about the potential and logistics of installing a wind turbine and or solar panels at their school  We will discuss the new Virginia Wind for Schools Program and work with hands on wind and solar energy curricula that can be used to integrate the renewable energy technology into the classroom  Lastly we will discuss other opportunities for students to apply energy concepts through engineering design challenges  This workshop covers technology for teachers and administrators with students in grades 3 8 Instructor   Cindy Kleveckis  Center for Wind Energy  James Madison University Putting the  T  in STEM Learning   Grades 3 8 Are you overwhelmed with the idea of integrating STEM tools in the classroom  Do you need help determining what tool would be the best fit for you and your students  Is cost the factor  Grade appropriateness  Subject area  Or maybe you need ideas on how integrate tools into your curriculum needs  Come learn and experience 5 STEM learning tools and how they can fa