ience  Niche Bots   Grades 3 4 In this hand s on workshop  participants will construct a Niche bot that contains a working circuit  The bot must represent its niche  have adaptations for its habitat  and characteristics of its animal type  The bot must include a working pager motor and move independently  Participants will create a unique name for each Niche bot and design a trading card using appropriate iPad apps  As a group  we will use the trading cards to discuss each Niche bot s role in the food web  Target Virginia SOL Standards  Science 3 4  3 5  3 6  4 5  4 3  English 3 9  3 10  3 12  4 7  4 8  Math 3 9  4 6  4 7  C T 3 5 2  C T 3 5 10  C T 3 5 11 Supporting Virginia SOL Standards  C T 3 5    This workshop covers science for teachers with students in grades 3 4  Instructors     Meg Swecker Instructional Technology Resource Teacher  Roanoke County Public Schools Meg Swecker is the Coordinator of Technology Integration and an ITRT for Roanoke County Public Schools  She collaborates with K 8 teachers in the use of instructional technology  STEM  Children s Engineering  and Project Based Learning   James Decker  4th Grade Teacher  Green Valley Elementary School Not all about the trifold board  Building grit and curiosity through engineering design   Grades 5 8  Administrators It takes more than the traditional science fair to ensure that your students develop the digital age skills and habits of mind to make them great innovators and problem solvers  Learn how to overcome three critical barriers to student centered learning using free resources from the Army Educational Outreach Program  This workshop is hands on make it take it  and teachers leave with ideas they can use Monday morning  This workshop covers integrated stem for teachers and administrators with students in grades 5 8  Instructor   Jill Latchana  Assistant Program Manager  National Science Teachers Association Jill Latchana is a former middle school science teacher livin  the dream at the Nationa