of this hands on lesson  Strands  Through the implementation of STEM projects  teachers establish rigorous and relevant activities that support students in building cooperation  communication  and community  Attending this workshop will support teachers in meeting the needs of diverse learners through collaborative instruction and sustained technological leadership with creative out of the box instructional units   ITEEA  Strand 2  In class design challenges  student research presentations  cooperative groups  and or transitional work teams that increase STEM learning in the classroom are strategies that are also supported in this session  ITEEA  Strand 3  This workshop covers integrated STEM for teachers with students in grades 5 8  Instructors   Anne Moore  Teacher  Goochland Middle School Anne Moore teaches sixth and seventh grade Technology and STEM at Goochland Middle School  Colleagues refer to her classroom as  serious fun  as she integrates STEM activities that keep students engaged and excited to learn  Anne is a recent recipient of the Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching and the 2015 Presidential Innovation Award for Environmental Educators  In 2012  Anne traveled to New Zealand through a Fund for Teachers grant to study bio diversity  sustainability  and to work with Ornithology Experts   Lisa Brown  Gifted Resource Teacher  Goochland Elementary School Lisa Brown is a gifted resource teacher and STEM advocate at Goochland Elementary School  At her school  Lisa has conceived and brought to fruition an annual Full STEAM Ahead Day  STEAM gardens  and is instrumental in planning the countywide STEM Camp each summer  She has been a past presenter at Virginia Association of the Gifted conference and Virginia Children s Engineering Conferences  Think  Sketch  Print   3D Printing in Algebra and Geometry   Grades 7 8 Capture the excitement of Algebra and Geometry and make connections by using 3D printing in the classroom  Engage s