covery  analysis  and drawing evidence based conclusions  Users can easily manipulate datasets to explore multiple attributes and create graphs  In this session  participants will learn how to set up a class in Tuva  find pre made activities for students  and create new lessons specific to your needs  Cross curricular applications will be presented for both upper elementary and middle school students  Tuva applies to all Scientific Investigation  Reasoning  and Logic SOLs  3 1  4 1  5 1  etc  as it gives students an opportunity to analyze data and draw conclusions  Tuva is also a great tool for teachers to use when teaching the Statistics SOLs specific to each grade in math  4 14  5 16  6 15 etc  Finally  Tuva has datasets related history  economics  and culture that could be used to draw connections with the humanities  This workshop covers Technology for teachers in grades 3 8  Instructors   Tracy Proffitt  Fourth Grade Gifted Teacher  R S  Payne Elementary  Lynchburg City Schools Tracy Proffitt teaches fourth grade math and science at Lynchburg City Schools  Gifted Opportunities Center  She has also taught both fourth and fifth grade inclusion classes  When she s not planning math lessons or searching for new science experiments  Tracy enjoys running  writing  hiking  and spending time with her husband  daughter  7  and son  3   Ruth Erquiaga  Sixth Grade Math Teacher  Liberty Christian Academy 2015 STEM Workshops 3D Printing in a Middle School Makerspace   Grades 5 8  Administrators 3D printing  Moving students from Replicator to Creator  lecture presentation 3D printers are absolutely mesmerizing  They light up and make wonderful sounds  Students of all ages are drawn to the idea of a 3D printers  They want to try it out but they have no idea how to do it  During this session we will walk you through the hurdles we encountered once we added a 3D printer into our Makerspace  We will share with you how we are slowly moving our students from just printing what someone else made to creating their own original creations to print  We will even show you how to digitize yourself to 3D print  This workshop covers technology for teachers and administrators with students in grades 5 8  Instructors   Susan Jinks  Ph  D  Instructional Technology Specialist  Falls Church City Public School  Dr  Susan Jinks is an instructional technology specialist at Mary Ellen Henderson Middle School  MEH  in Falls Church City  VA  Jinks helped her school deploy a 1 1 laptop program during the 2014 school year  In addition  she successfully co wrote a grant to establish a Makerspace in the school library  She recently became a Google Educator and Google for Education Certified Trainer  Her doctoral work focused on the factors that lead to the perception of learning within a graduate online course   Lori Fogle  Librarian Media Specialist  Falls Church City Public School 2015 STEM Workshops 3D Printing in a Middle School Makerspace   Grades 5 8  Administrators 3D printing  Moving students from Replicator to Creator  lecture presentation 3D printers are absolutely mesmerizing  They light up and make wonderful sounds  Students of all ages are drawn to the idea of a 3D printers  They want to try it out but they have no idea how to do it  During this session we will walk you through the hurdles we encountered once we added a 3D printer into our Makerspace  We will share with you how we are slowly moving our students from just printing what someone else made to creating their own original creations to print  We will even show you how to digitize yourself to 3D print  This workshop covers technology for teachers and administrators with students in grades 5 8  Instructors   Susan Jinks  Ph  D  Instructional Technology Specialist  Falls Church City Public School  Dr  Susan Jinks is an instructional technology specialist at Mary Ellen Henderson Middle School  MEH  in Falls Church City  VA  Jinks helped her school deploy a 1 1 laptop program during the 2014 schoo