s using todaysmeet com were relevant to discuss various problems that students were having while navigating equations  Students gave feedback on each other s art  learning  through the project  slope and y intercept form and key elements to linear functions from a very elementary understanding  6th   8th grade curriculum  Students wrote a synopsis of what the artistic elements meant to them and how they chose to use materials and various elements to set the tone of the work of art  Students wrote a paper using google docs relating the art to the mathematics in a formal five paragraph format  Attendees will take away all handouts rubrics  etc  Numerous examples of student work will be used to explain the project and extend attendees view of what students can do when given the freedom to think critically and creatively  The session will culminate brainstorming ways that this project can be enhanced or ways students  work can be published  This workshop covers mathematics for teachers with students in grades 5 8  Instructor   Tabatha Myers  Teacher  Albemarle County Public Schools Tabatha has been teaching mathematics and science for ACPS for 12 years and has an B S  in Liberal Science  Elementary Ed  from Longwood University  In 2007  she received her Master of Education and Math Specialist Endorsement from the University of Virginia  She has taught sixth grade math her entire career  primarily located at the AVID demo school Jack Jouett Middle  She teaches a wide array of both math and science curriculum including all of middle school mathematics Blending Art  Language Arts and Linear Equations   Grades 5 8 Participants will all be given the same equations and blank paper to graph with NO guidance regarding scale factor  After equations are graphed  instructions will be to create a piece of art that uses color and texture to relate to some aspect of their life  As art is completed  comparisons of the  chevron  that emerges will be relevant to relating the art to the 