 and the importance of using a budget  During the activity M Ms are used to represent income and expenses  Students are encouraged to have money left over at the end of the activity  Participants will receive a copy of the lesson plan and a sample package of the budgeting activity that can be reproduced over and over again  This lesson plan can be used for grades 4 and up  and covers Virginia SOLs 4 4b  5 4  and 6 3  This workshop covers mathematics for teachers with students in grades 3 8  Instructor   Sarah Landram  Community Financial Educator  DuPont Community Credit Union Sarah Landram is the Community Financial Educator at DuPont Community Credit Union  In her role as educator  she works with local schools  and other organizations to bring financial education lessons to much of the Central Shenandoah Valley  In 2012  she became a Certified Financial Counselor through the Credit Union National Association s FiCep program  She is a 2012 graduate of the Harrisonburg Rockingham Leadership program and a two time winner of the Desjardin Youth Financial Education Award for the state of Virginia  Sarah is also a certified trainer for the National Endowment for Financial Education  Prior to joining the Financial Education department  Sarah worked for 17 years in the Retail area at DCCU Budgeting with M Ms   Grades 3 8 During this workshop participants will get to experience a hands on budget lesson that uses multiplication  addition  and subtraction  This lesson will introduce students to budgeting concepts like income and expenses  and the importance of using a budget  During the activity M Ms are used to represent income and expenses  Students are encouraged to have money left over at the end of the activity  Participants will receive a copy of the lesson plan and a sample package of the budgeting activity that can be reproduced over and over again  This lesson plan can be used for grades 4 and up  and covers Virginia SOLs 4 4b  5 4  and 6 3  This workshop covers mat