ey  Library Media Specialist  MCPS   Belview Elementary School  Diane Naff  Supervisor of Gifted Programs  Montgomery County Public School Critical Creative Thinking and Standards of Learning do Mix  Easy recipes to make it work in your classroom   Grades 3 4  5 6  Administrators Discover how easy it is to integrate STEM and children s engineering into your existing curriculum  In this interactive session  presenters will demonstrate the use of VA DOE Design Briefs and use children s literature to encourage critical thinking and problem solving while targeting specific standards  Participants will have access to a repository of design briefs and hands on activities to enhance their daily instruction  This Workshop Covers   Integrated STEM Instructors   Terri Vangelos  Gifted Resource Teacher  Montgomery County Public Schools An experienced educator with 15  years in the classroom  who has focused on gifted education by providing extension and challenge for K 5 students and support to their regular ed teachers during the past 6 years  Mrs  Vangelos was named Region IV Gifted Teacher of the Year by the Virginia Association for the Gifted in 2015   Becca Rainey  Library Media Specialist  MCPS   Belview Elementary School  Diane Naff  Supervisor of Gifted Programs  Montgomery County Public School Discover how easy it is to integrate STEM and children s engineering into your existing curriculum  In this interactive session  presenters will demonstrate the use of VA DOE Design Briefs and use children s literature to encourage critical thinking and problem solving while targeting specific standards  Participants will have access to a repository of design briefs and hands on activities to enhance their daily instruction This Workshop Covers   Integrated STEM Instructors Terri Vangelos  Gifted Resource Teacher  Montgomery County Public Schools An experienced educator with 15  years in the classroom  who has focused on gifted education by providing extension and challenge for K 5 students and support to their regular ed teachers during the past 6 years  Mrs  Vangelos was named Region IV Gifted Teacher of the Year by the Virginia Association for the Gifted in 2015 An experienced educator with 15  years in the classroom  who has focused on gifted education by providing extension and challenge for K 5 students and support to their regular ed teachers during the past 6 years  Mrs  Vangelos was named Region IV Gifted Teacher of the Year by the Virginia Association for the Gifted in 2015 Becca Rainey  Library Media Specialist  MCPS   Belview Elementary School  Diane Naff  Supervisor of Gifted Programs  Montgomery County Public School  Developing STEM Initiatives in the Rural School District   Grades 3 8  Administrators In order to implement an effective STEM program in a rural school district  one must understand the nature and needs of such unique communities  This session will discuss the five components of developing a high school STEM program  The first component will focus on the use of incorporating data so that the division recognizes the need for STEM initiatives  This may even include assisting in dissolving traditional district boundaries  Component two will focus on identifying stakeholders who would develop a steering committee  community partnerships  community  local industry and post secondary education  and an advocate for the process  This component will show that a rural community needs to come together with resources to create a lasting and effective STEM education infrastructure  This leads into the third component  Professional development and fourth component  Technology  It is extremely important that educators within the division adopt and are trained in the effective use of technology and distance learning  The final component is the capstone of the program which includes internships and the inclusion of CTE programs  This workshop covers integrated STEM for teachers and administrators with students in grades 3 8  Instructors     Thomas Johnson III High School Assistant Principal STEM Program Chair Accomack County Public Schools Mr  Thomas Johnson III is currently serving as the Assistant Principal for Nandua Middle School in Accomack County  He is the leading advocate and chairperson of the Accomack County Public Schools STEM Academy which is starting the third successful year in operation  Mr  Johnson has earned a Bachelor of Science in Mathematics from Longwood College  a Masters in Education from North Georgia State University and Educational Specialist degree in Educational Leadership from Jones University   Rebecca Johnson  Facilitator of Gifted Resources Accomack County Public Schools Developing STEM Initiatives in the Rural School District   Grades 3 8  Administrators In order to implement an effective STEM program in a rural school district  one must understand the nature and needs of such unique communities  This session will discuss the five components of developing a high school STEM program  The first component will focus on the use of incorporating data so that the division recognizes the need for STEM initiatives  This may even include assisting in dissolving traditional district boundaries  Component two will focus on identifying stakeholders who would develop a steering committee  community partnerships  community  local industry and post secondary education  and an advocate for the process  This component will show that a rural community needs to come together with resources to create a lasting and effective STEM education infrastructure  This leads into the third component  Professional development and fourth component  Technology  It is extremely important that educators within the division adopt and are trained in the effective use of technology and distance learning  The final component is the capstone of the program which includes internships and the inclusion of CTE programs  This workshop covers integrated STEM for teachers and administrators with student