ations for its habitat  and characteristics of its animal type  The bot must include a working pager motor and move independently  Participants will create a unique name for each Niche bot and design a trading card using appropriate iPad apps  As a group  we will use the trading cards to discuss each Niche bot s role in the food web  Target Virginia SOL Standards  Science 3 4  3 5  3 6  4 5  4 3  English 3 9  3 10  3 12  4 7  4 8  Math 3 9  4 6  4 7  C T 3 5 2  C T 3 5 10  C T 3 5 11 Supporting Virginia SOL Standards  C T 3 5    This workshop covers science for teachers with students in grades 3 4  Instructors     Meg Swecker Instructional Technology Resource Teacher  Roanoke County Public Schools Meg Swecker is the Coordinator of Technology Integration and an ITRT for Roanoke County Public Schools  She collaborates with K 8 teachers in the use of instructional technology  STEM  Children s Engineering  and Project Based Learning   James Decker  4th Grade Teacher  Green Valley Elementary School Niche Bots   Grades 3 4 In this hand s on workshop  participants will construct a Niche bot that contains a working circuit  The bot must represent its niche  have adaptations for its habitat  and characteristics of its animal type  The bot must include a working pager motor and move independently  Participants will create a unique name for each Niche bot and design a trading card using appropriate iPad apps  As a group  we will use the trading cards to discuss each Niche bot s role in the food web  Target Virginia SOL Standards  Science 3 4  3 5  3 6  4 5  4 3  English 3 9  3 10  3 12  4 7  4 8  Math 3 9  4 6  4 7  C T 3 5 2  C T 3 5 10  C T 3 5 11 Supporting Virginia SOL Standards  C T 3 5    This workshop covers science for teachers with students in grades 3 4  Instructors     Meg Swecker Instructional Technology Resource Teacher  Roanoke County Public Schools Meg Swecker is the Coordinator of Technology Integration and an ITRT for Roanoke County Public Schools  She collabo