chers and administrators with students in grades 5 8  Instructor   Stephen Shumaker  Education Consultant  LEGO Education Stephen has a passion for learning and believes in the strength of knowledge gained and retained through Hands On applied learning  He enjoys construction  history and the outdoors  As time permits he takes the family on nature walks and outdoor excursions  He also enjoys hunting with his daughter for arrowheads and wild game Overcoming Obstacles to Learning by Using Robotics   Grades 5 8 This workshop will have you complete a simple obstacle course using the LEGO Education EV3 Robot  Attendees will program their robot to complete the course while using math  logical thinking  trial and error  perseverance  collaboration  and communication skills  See how your students can overcome barriers to learning through total engagement with robotics  This workshop covers mathematics for teachers and administrators with students in grades 5 8  Instructor   Stephen Shumaker  Education Consultant  LEGO Education Stephen has a passion for learning and believes in the strength of knowledge gained and retained through Hands On applied learning  He enjoys construction  history and the outdoors  As time permits he takes the family on nature walks and outdoor excursions  He also enjoys hunting with his daughter for arrowheads and wild game This workshop covers mathematics for teachers and administrators with students in grades 5 8    Stephen has a passion for learning and believes in the strength of knowledge gained and retained through Hands On applied learning  He enjoys construction  history and the outdoors  As time permits he takes the family on nature walks and outdoor excursions  He also enjoys hunting with his daughter for arrowheads and wild game Stephen has a passion for learning and believes in the strength of knowledge gained and retained through Hands On applied learning  He enjoys construction  history and the outdoors  As time permits he takes the f