nd operation of the catapult will be discussed  Two small  model versions  Roman and medieval  of the catapult will be demonstrated by throwing marshmallows  This workshop covers history of engineering for teachers of students in grades 7 8  Instructor   Col Wayne Neel  Ph  D  Department of Mechanical Engineering  Virginia Military Institute Willard Wayne Neel  Ph D  PE  Professor in the Mechanical Engineering Department at the Virginia Military Institute  He has degrees in physics and mechanical engineering from the University of South Florida and N C  State University  respectively  Besides teaching for the past forty six years he is interested in ancient and medieval technology Roman Catapult   Grades 7 8 The presentation will entail a quick overview  using PowerPoint  of the historical context of a 4th century CE Roman catapult and its legacy into the middle ages  The geometry  construction and operation of the catapult will be discussed  Two small  model versions  Roman and medieval  of the catapult will be demonstrated by throwing marshmallows  This workshop covers history of engineering for teachers of students in grades 7 8  Instructor   Col Wayne Neel  Ph  D  Department of Mechanical Engineering  Virginia Military Institute Willard Wayne Neel  Ph D  PE  Professor in the Mechanical Engineering Department at the Virginia Military Institute  He has degrees in physics and mechanical engineering from the University of South Florida and N C  State University  respectively  Besides teaching for the past forty six years he is interested in ancient and medieval technology The presentation will entail a quick overview  using PowerPoint  of the historical context of a 4th century CE Roman catapult and its legacy into the middle ages  The geometry  construction and operation of the catapult will be discussed  Two small  model versions  Roman and medieval  of the catapult will be demonstrated by throwing marshmallows This workshop covers history of engineering for teach