 through research  the study of biomes  technology integration  packaging engineering  and mathematical components  Come join this interactive atmosphere and participate in the Ultimate Survivor Challenge  Educators will leave the session with resources to create individual versions of this hands on lesson  Strands  Through the implementation of STEM projects  teachers establish rigorous and relevant activities that support students in building cooperation  communication  and community  Attending this workshop will support teachers in meeting the needs of diverse learners through collaborative instruction and sustained technological leadership with creative out of the box instructional units   ITEEA  Strand 2  In class design challenges  student research presentations  cooperative groups  and or transitional work teams that increase STEM learning in the classroom are strategies that are also supported in this session  ITEEA  Strand 3  This workshop covers integrated STEM for teachers with students in grades 5 8  Instructors   Anne Moore  Teacher  Goochland Middle School Anne Moore teaches sixth and seventh grade Technology and STEM at Goochland Middle School  Colleagues refer to her classroom as  serious fun  as she integrates STEM activities that keep students engaged and excited to learn  Anne is a recent recipient of the Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching and the 2015 Presidential Innovation Award for Environmental Educators  In 2012  Anne traveled to New Zealand through a Fund for Teachers grant to study bio diversity  sustainability  and to work with Ornithology Experts   Lisa Brown  Gifted Resource Teacher  Goochland Elementary School Lisa Brown is a gifted resource teacher and STEM advocate at Goochland Elementary School  At her school  Lisa has conceived and brought to fruition an annual Full STEAM Ahead Day  STEAM gardens  and is instrumental in planning the countywide STEM Camp each summer  She has been a past presenter at Virginia Association of the Gifted conference and Virginia Children s Engineering Conferences Think Outside  Survive Inside the Box   Grades 5 8 Can your team survive in the wilderness  Randomly picking a location  biome  and other challenges  teams develop the  Ultimate Survival Box  that will help them conquer the elements  With dozens of scenario combinations  each team will research  design  and develop the tools they can take with them  while meeting set parameters and constraints  Along with applying the Engineering Design Process  the challenge also integrates STEM through research  the study of biomes  technology integration  packaging engineering  and mathematical components  Come join this interactive atmosphere and participate in the Ultimate Survivor Challenge  Educators will leave the session with resources to create individual versions of this hands on lesson  Strands  Through the implementation of STEM projects  teachers establish rigorous and relevant activities that support students in building cooperation  communication  and community  Attending this workshop will support teachers in meeting the needs of diverse learners through collaborative instruction and sustained technological leadership with creative out of the box instructional units   ITEEA  Strand 2  In class design challenges  student research presentations  cooperative groups  and or transitional work teams that increase STEM learning in the classroom are strategies that are also supported in this session  ITEEA  Strand 3  This workshop covers integrated STEM for teachers with students in grades 5 8  Instructors   Anne Moore  Teacher  Goochland Middle School Anne Moore teaches sixth and seventh grade Technology and STEM at Goochland Middle School  Colleagues refer to her classroom as  serious fun  as she integrates STEM activities that keep students engaged and excited to learn  Anne is a recent recipient of the Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching and 